The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, November 25, 2002  Business Briefs																								 New Delhi, Nov. 24: A steep increase in the prices of vegetables and fruits pushed up inflation for the fourth consecutive week to 3.27 per cent in the week ended November 9. Point-to-point price changes as measured by the wholesale price index (WPI) rose 0.13 per cent from the week-ago level of 3.14 per cent broadly due to a substantial hike in the price of essential primary articles. 																								 New Delhi, Nov. 24: Two-wheeler sales surged by 23 per cent in the first seven months of this fiscal. A total of 28.76 lakh two-wheelers were sold during April-October this year, against 23.39 lakh vehicles a year ago, data compiled by the Society of Indian Automobile Manufacturers (SIAM) showed. 																								 New Delhi, Nov. 24: Network publishing software major Adobe India will grow 50 per cent in the next six months in terms of headcount to supplement its current 150 professionals to work primarily on the next version of Framemaker 7.0, a senior company official said today. 
